    "en": {
      "title": "Three protestors arrested in Sri Lanka for selling stolen items from President\u2019s House",
      "author": "Neshella Perera",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Three protesters in Sri Lanka have been arrested for attempting to sell gold-plated brass curtain sockets that were allegedly stolen from the President\u2019s House in Colombo after protestors stormed the place on July 09.",
        "\u201cWe received a complaint from Rajagiriya over three individuals selling items from the President\u2019s House,\u201d the officer in charge (OIC) of the Welikada police station said.",
        "The suspects, aged 28, 34 and 37 and residing at Obeysekarapura in Rajagiriya,\u00a0 had nabbed forty gold-plated brass curtain sockets.",
        "Police had launched separate investigations into the storming and occupation of several state-owned buildings by protestors. Sensitive evidence is now being gathered, police said.",
        "The three arrested protestors have been\u00a0 handed overr to the Colombo (North) Criminal Investigation Division.",
        "Further investigations are underway in collaboration with the Criminal Investigation Department (CID) and the Scene of Crime Officers (SOCO) department, police said.",
        "The Presidential Secretariat which was reclaimed by the authorities prior to its handover by protestors on July 22 has now resumed work and renovations are underway. (Colombo/Jul25/2022)"
      ],
